# 📍 Day 17 — VPC (Deep Dive - Part 1)

## 🎯 Objective

Understand core networking components inside AWS VPC.

---

## 📌 Topics Covered

### 🔹 CIDR & IP Addressing

* Defines IP range of VPC
* Important for subnet planning

---

### 🔹 Public vs Private IP

* Public IP → accessible from internet
* Private IP → internal communication

---

### 🔹 Default VPC vs Custom VPC

* Default → ready-to-use
* Custom → full control over networking

---

### 🔹 Subnets

* Public Subnet → internet accessible
* Private Subnet → no direct internet

---

### 🔹 Internet Gateway (IGW)

* Enables internet access
* Attached to VPC

---

### 🔹 Route Tables

* Controls traffic routing
* Defines paths (local / internet)

---

### 🔹 Bastion Host

* Used to securely access private instances
* Acts as jump server

---

### 🔹 NAT Instance

* Allows private subnet instances to access internet
* No inbound internet access

---

## 💡 Key Learnings

* Networking defines architecture behavior
* Public vs Private subnet is critical
* Routing + gateways control traffic flow

---

## 🚧 Challenges Faced

* Understanding routing flow
* Visualizing subnet + gateway connections

---

